    <text x="640" y="270" fill="#f87171" font-size="22" text-anchor="middle">✕</text>

    <text x="350" y="360" fill="#a1a1aa" font-size="13" text-anchor="middle">The same logic (dense acquisition price = support/resistance) was applied both times, but</text>
    <text x="350" y="380" fill="#a1a1aa" font-size="13" text-anchor="middle">what separated a cluster that held for three years from one broken in months wasn't density — it was who was in it</text>
